OL,3,CThe women haunted by forced adoptions
OL,4,Clooking for answers
OL,6,FIn 1967, Jill Killington, from
OL,7,FNorwich, was 17, unmarried and
OL,8,Fpregnant. Despite being in a steady
OL,9,Frelationship, she was sworn to secrecy
OL,10,Fby her "distraught parents".
OL,12,FJill Killington, who was forced into
OL,13,Fgiving up her son for adoption, told
OL,14,FITV News she and thousands of others
OL,15,Fwere treated in an 'unacceptable' and
OL,16,F'terribly cruel' way
OL,18,FWhat followed was a sequence of events
OL,19,Fthat would have life-long consequences.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/18
